cs.LG, cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.RO 

The paper proposes a new method for Multi-Agent Reinforcement Learning in cooperative control settings. This involves addressing challenges such as non-stationarity, credit assignment, exploration, and coordination. The paper uses deep learning techniques and a model of system dynamics to guide the learning process. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with control systems, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.RO (Robotics).
